Name: lethal congenital contracture syndrome 1
Definition: A lethal congenital contracture syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the mRNA export mediator GLE1 on chromosome 9q34.

Name: lethal congenital contracture syndrome 2
Definition: A lethal congenital contracture syndrome that can be that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the ERBB3 gene on chromosome 12q13.

Name: obsolete DMD-related dilated cardiomyopathy
Definition: A dilated cardiomyopathy that has_material_basis_in mutations in the DMD gene.

Name: lethal congenital contracture syndrome 3
Definition: A lethal congenital contracture syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PIP5K1C gene on chromosome 19p13.
Synonym: Israeli Bedouin type B multiple contracture syndrome

Name: lethal congenital contracture syndrome 4
Definition: A lethal congenital contracture syndrome that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the MYBPC1 gene on chromosome 12q23.
Synonym: Israeli Bedouin type B multiple contracture syndrome
